property.name: text
property.value:
The system consist of 3 independent power supplies. The output voltage, maximum current, and the delay between startup and actual turn-on and shutdown and actual shutdown can be adjusted via parameters. The supplies all monitor their output current and if the maximum current is exceeded they will send a fault indication to the network and will themselves initiate a local shutdown.
The loads can be adjusted for resistance (default is 100 ohms) and for a time at which the load current doubles. This may be used to simulate a fault if the doubling of current exceeds the maximum supply current.
The supervisor can issue 2 startup commands at parameterized times, and a single fault command at a parameterized time.
The bridge models the multicast behavior of the network (but not network timing).
The plot actors monitor the voltage of all power supplies and the current of supply #1. The event monitor displays the internal state of supply #1 and the startup, shutdown, fault command events from the supervisor and the fault indication input to supply #1.

property.name: text
property.value:
The composite actor Supply Control represents the microprocessor-based internal control structure of the power supply. The internals of this composite actor operate in a PTides director.
The other blocks represent analog or FPGA implemented functions configured by the Supply Control but operating under timing controlled by the environment (one level up) DE director.

property.name: text
property.value: Models the charging of the output capacitor in the power supply so that the actual voltage output does not change instataneously with the requested voltage.

property.name: text
property.value: Ensures that only a single event is produced on true and no event on false

svg.text: The model represents the state behavior of the power supply and how it reacts to startup, shutdown, and fault conditions. The refinements of state 1 and 3 illustrate the use of delay actors to enable timed sequencing of a set of power supplies.

property.name: text
property.value: Models the external load on the power supply. The resistance is a parameter. The parameeter timeToDoubleCurrent sets the DE time at which the current is scaled up by x2 in the modla model.

property.name: text
property.value: This actor models the multicast behavior of the bridge. It does not model the timing behavior. Thus a fault indication FI2 is not distributed to output F2 but only to F1 and F3.
